    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-04-09T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-04-09T13:00:00-05:00" n="506"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760D.6111/4–948: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Legation in Finland</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-04-09T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 9, 1948—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>79. You are requested make discreet inquiry, possibly through your Fr or Brit
                    colleagues, to learn with certainty whether any secret agreement with USSR was
                    made or contemplated in connection mutual defense pact. (Moscow’s 8 Apr 7 to
                        Helsinki).<note n="1" xml:id="d506fn1">Not printed; in it Ambassador Smith
                        suggested the possibility of secret protocols to Soviet-Finnish Treaty since
                        his evidence indicated such protocols accompanied other Soviet mutual aid
                        pacts (760D.6111/4–748).</note> Authoritative comments <pb facs="0798"
                        n="777" xml:id="pg_777"/> on implications and implementation of Article Two
                    would be of interest.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
